<p>A body-in-white passes through more than four thousand spot welds before it ever reaches the paint shop, and every
    one of those welds is a small opportunity for electrode wear, misaligned tip dress timing, or a weld schedule that
    drifted slightly out of tune. Body shop engineers have traditionally managed this through fixed maintenance
    intervals and periodic destructive testing, which either over-services healthy weld guns or misses a gun that's
    degrading faster than the schedule assumes. AI-driven weld optimization tracks every weld gun's performance in real
    time, tunes schedules automatically, and predicts electrode wear before it produces an undersized nugget. Body shop
    engineers can <a href="https://calendly.com/contact-heavyvehicleinspection/30min">book a demo</a> to see weld quality
    monitoring running across a live production cell.</p>
