<div class="bsw-section">
    <div class="bsw-h2">Why Fixed Tip Dress Schedules Leave Quality Gaps</div>
    <div class="bsw-text">A fixed tip dress interval assumes every electrode wears at the same rate, but material
        thickness variation, gun angle, and even ambient conditions all change how fast a tip actually degrades.
        Dressing too early wastes consumables and cycle time; dressing too late risks an undersized nugget that passes
        visually but fails a peel test months later. AI weld monitoring tracks the actual electrical signature of each
        weld cycle, so tip dress timing adjusts to real wear instead of a calendar assumption.</div>
</div>
