<div class="bsw-section">
    <div class="bsw-h2">Where the Cost Savings Actually Come From</div>
    <div class="bsw-text">Body shop managers tend to focus tip dress optimization purely on consumable spend, but the
        bigger line item is usually unplanned downtime avoided. A gun that fails mid-shift because a tip wore out faster
        than the schedule assumed forces a changeover that stops the cell, not just that one station, and cascading
        stoppages on a synchronized body line are far more expensive than the consumable itself. Predictive tip dress
        timing converts those unplanned stops into planned changeovers scheduled during natural line gaps, which
        protects throughput in a way that raw consumable savings numbers alone don't capture. Combined with fewer
        destructive test failures and less rework on marginal welds, the total cost impact typically runs well beyond
        the electrode budget line.</div>
</div>
